headline: Home Depot Rises After Earnings. Why the Winter Storm Could Boost the Stock.
summary: Home Depot  stock was rising Tuesday after the home-improvement retailer reported better-than-expected earnings for its fiscal fourth quarter.  Home Depot reported adjusted earnings of $2.58 a share as revenue slipped 3.8% from a year ago to $38.2 billion.  The fourth quarter of the company’s fiscal 2025 consisted of 13 weeks, compared with 14 weeks for the prior year.
